    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Note by J.M. Reynolds in <ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>20.726</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2014"/>, n. <citedRange>15</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>064910</citedRange></bibl>.
                    </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                    <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" cert="low"><name nymRef="#Χαρ_" cert="low"><seg part="I"><orig>χαρ</orig></seg></name></persName>

	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p> غير قابل للترجمة بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Those three letters were not mentioned by other scholars before Reynolds. Probably older than those of <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr064920</ref>, they 
                    seem to belong to the earliest use of the panel, before it being cut off at left. Meaningless by themselves, they might be the beginning of a personal 
                    name, either abbreviated, unfinished or erased.</p>
	           <p>Reynolds' reading was controlled by Rosamilia with the help of a cast kept in Rome. On the original, the letters might perhaps be seen only under special light. 
	           Struffolino's very good photo allows now to guess the letters, which are situated under the initial chi of line 2 of <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr064910</ref>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
